Subject: [Cse-grad-announce] YES Montreal Networking Event for Students Interested in a Career in Software Engineering From: Halina Monkiewicz <halina@encs.concordia.ca> Date: 2013/10/17 9:42 To: grad-announce@cse.concordia.ca
-------- Original Message -------- Subject: YES Montreal Networking Event for Students Interested in a Career in Software Engineering Date: Thu, 17 Oct 2013 09:37:24 -0400 From: Stephanie Zacharkiw <szacharkiw@yesmontreal.ca> To: halina@cs.concordia.ca <halina@cs.concordia.ca>
Hi Halina
I was talking to Antonella Nizzola yesterday about our Career Night in Software Engineering. Originally there was a $20 cost to attend, however, we are making it free for students. Antonella is not in the office today to relay the new information to the students. Would you be able to convey this information to your students is there another person I should talk to?
This is an event that helps individuals, primarily students and new graduates gain insight in their chosen Career, as well as promotes an opportunity for Networking. Even though this event is part of our Women in Technology program, men are encouraged to attend. The focus will not be on Women in Tech.
Here are the details of where and when:
When: Thursday, Oct 17th, 6:30pm-8:30pm
Where: YES office (666 Sherbrooke Street West (corner University) on the 7th floor – the closest Metro stop is McGill, on the green line). There is parking on the street.
Outline of the event: The Panel consists of 3 Presenters (see attached Bio’s) and will begin by spending 10-15 minutes highlighting details/experiences from his/her career path. Afterwards, a question-and-answer session is held where the participants can ask various questions to the panel to get the Industry’s “inside scoop”. At the end of the evening, the participants will be given an opportunity to network with each other and the panelists.
Registration: Doors open at 6:00 or call Reception (514-878-9788) for more information.
Please feel free to contact me if you have any further information.
Stephanie
Stephanie Zacharkiw, M.A. Career Advisor YES Montreal (Youth Employment Services) 666 Sherbrooke Street West, Suite 700 Montreal, Quebec H3A 1E7 Office: (514) 878-9788 Ext. 325 Fax: (514) 878-9950 www.yesmontreal.ca
Please note that our Drop In hours have changed and is now being offered from 12:00 PM to 1:00 PM Monday through Friday.
